{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Hi. Today, I'm going to take you through glimpses"},{"time":2000,"text":"of about eight of my projects,"},{"time":4000,"text":"done in collaboration with Danish artist Soren Pors."},{"time":7000,"text":"We call ourselves Pors and Rao,"},{"time":9000,"text":"and we live and work in India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11000,"text":"I'd like to begin with my very first object,"},{"time":14000,"text":"which I call \"The Uncle Phone.\""},{"time":16000,"text":"And it was inspired by my uncle's peculiar habit"},{"time":19000,"text":"of constantly asking me to do things for him,"},{"time":21000,"text":"almost like I were an extension of his body --"},{"time":23000,"text":"to turn on the lights or to bring him a glass of water,"},{"time":25000,"text":"a pack of cigarettes."},{"time":27000,"text":"And as I grew up, it became worse and worse,"},{"time":29000,"text":"And I started to think of it as a form of control."},{"time":31000,"text":"But of course, I could never say anything,"},{"time":33000,"text":"because the uncle is a respected figure"},{"time":35000,"text":"in the Indian family."},{"time":37000,"text":"And the situation that irked me and mystified me the most"},{"time":40000,"text":"was his use of a landline telephone."},{"time":42000,"text":"He would hold on to the receiver and expect me to dial a number for him."},{"time":45000,"text":"And so as a response and as a gift to my uncle,"},{"time":48000,"text":"I made him \"The Uncle Phone.\""},{"time":50000,"text":"It's so long that it requires two people to use it."},{"time":53000,"text":"It's exactly the way my uncle uses a phone that's designed for one person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57000,"text":"But the problem is that, when I left home and went to college,"},{"time":60000,"text":"I started missing his commands."},{"time":62000,"text":"And so I made him a golden typewriter"},{"time":64000,"text":"through which he could dispense his commands"},{"time":66000,"text":"to nephews and nieces around the world as an email."},{"time":69000,"text":"So what he had to do was take a piece of paper, roll it into the carriage,"},{"time":72000,"text":"type his email or command and pull the paper out."},{"time":75000,"text":"This device would automatically send the intended person"},{"time":78000,"text":"the letter as an email."},{"time":80000,"text":"So here you can see, we embedded a lot of electronics"},{"time":83000,"text":"that understands all of the mechanical actions"},{"time":85000,"text":"and converts it to digital."},{"time":87000,"text":"So my uncle is only dealing with a mechanical interface."},{"time":90000,"text":"And of course, the object had to be very grand and have a sense of ritualism,"},{"time":93000,"text":"the way my uncle likes it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"The next work is a sound-sensitive installation"},{"time":98000,"text":"that we affectionately call \"The Pygmies.\""},{"time":101000,"text":"And we wanted to work with a notion of being"},{"time":103000,"text":"surrounded by a tribe of very shy, sensitive and sweet creatures."},{"time":107000,"text":"So how it works is we have these panels, which we have on the wall,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and behind them, we have these little creatures which hide."},{"time":113000,"text":"And as soon as it's silent, they sort of creep out."},{"time":116000,"text":"And if it's even more silent, they stretch their necks out."},{"time":118000,"text":"And at the slightest sound, they hide back again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"So we had these panels on three walls of a room."},{"time":124000,"text":"And we had over 500 of these little pygmies hiding behind them."},{"time":127000,"text":"So this is how it works."},{"time":129000,"text":"This is a video prototype."},{"time":131000,"text":"So when it's quiet, it's sort of coming out from behind the panels."},{"time":134000,"text":"And they hear like humans do, or real creatures do."},{"time":136000,"text":"So they get immune to sounds that scare them after awhile."},{"time":139000,"text":"And they don't react to background sounds."},{"time":142000,"text":"You'll hear a train in moment that they don't react to."},{"time":145000,"text":"(Noise)"},{"time":147000,"text":"But they react to foreground sounds. You'll hear that in a second."},{"time":150000,"text":"(Whistling)"},{"time":155000,"text":"So we worked very hard"},{"time":157000,"text":"to make them as lifelike as possible."},{"time":161000,"text":"So each pygmy has its own behavior, psyche,"},{"time":163000,"text":"mood swings, personalities and so on."},{"time":166000,"text":"So this is a very early prototype."},{"time":168000,"text":"Of course, it got much better after that."},{"time":170000,"text":"And we made them react to people,"},{"time":172000,"text":"but we found that people were being quite playful and childlike with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"This is a video installation called \"The Missing Person.\""},{"time":179000,"text":"And we were quite intrigued"},{"time":181000,"text":"with playing with the notion of invisibility."},{"time":183000,"text":"How would it be possible to experience a sense of invisibility?"},{"time":186000,"text":"So we worked with a company"},{"time":188000,"text":"that specializes in camera surveillance,"},{"time":190000,"text":"and we asked them to develop a piece of software with us,"},{"time":193000,"text":"using a camera"},{"time":195000,"text":"that could look at people in the room, track them"},{"time":197000,"text":"and replace one person with the background, rendering them invisible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"So I'm just going to show you a very early prototype."},{"time":203000,"text":"On the right side you can see my colleague Soren,"},{"time":205000,"text":"who's actually in the space."},{"time":207000,"text":"And on the left side, you'll see the processed video"},{"time":209000,"text":"where the camera has made him invisible."},{"time":212000,"text":"Soren enters the room. Pop! He goes invisible."},{"time":215000,"text":"And you can see that the camera is tracking him and erasing."},{"time":218000,"text":"It's a very early video,"},{"time":220000,"text":"so we haven't yet dealt with the overlap and all of that,"},{"time":222000,"text":"but that got refined pretty soon, later."},{"time":225000,"text":"So how we used it was in a room where we had a camera looking into the space,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and we had one monitor, one on each wall."},{"time":231000,"text":"And as people walked into the room,"},{"time":233000,"text":"they would see themselves in the monitor, except with one difference:"},{"time":236000,"text":"one person was constantly invisible"},{"time":238000,"text":"wherever they moved in the room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"So this is a work called \"The Sun Shadow.\""},{"time":242000,"text":"And it was almost like a sheet of paper,"},{"time":245000,"text":"like a cutout of a childlike drawing"},{"time":247000,"text":"of an oil spill or a sun."},{"time":249000,"text":"And from the front, this object appeared to be very strong and robust,"},{"time":252000,"text":"and from the side, it almost seemed very weak."},{"time":255000,"text":"So people would walking into the room and they'd almost ignore it,"},{"time":258000,"text":"thinking it was some crap laying around."},{"time":260000,"text":"But as soon as they passed by,"},{"time":262000,"text":"it would start to climb up the wall in jerky fashion."},{"time":264000,"text":"And it would get exhausted, and it would collapse every time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"So this work"},{"time":271000,"text":"is a caricature of an upside-down man."},{"time":273000,"text":"His head is so heavy, full of heavy thoughts,"},{"time":275000,"text":"that it's sort of fallen into his hat,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and his body's grown out of him almost like a plant."},{"time":279000,"text":"Well what he does is he moves around"},{"time":281000,"text":"in a very drunken fashion on his head"},{"time":283000,"text":"in a very unpredictable and extremely slow movement."},{"time":286000,"text":"And it's kind of constrained by that circle."},{"time":289000,"text":"Because if that circle weren't there, and the floor was very even,"},{"time":292000,"text":"it would start to wander about in the space."},{"time":294000,"text":"And there's no wires."},{"time":296000,"text":"So I'll just show you an instance --"},{"time":298000,"text":"so when people enter the room, it activates this object."},{"time":300000,"text":"And it very slowly, over a few minutes,"},{"time":302000,"text":"sort of painfully goes up,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and then it gains momentum"},{"time":306000,"text":"and it looks like it's almost about to fall."},{"time":308000,"text":"And this is an important moment,"},{"time":310000,"text":"because we wanted to instill in the viewer"},{"time":312000,"text":"an instinct to almost go and help, or save the subject."},{"time":314000,"text":"But it doesn't really need it,"},{"time":316000,"text":"because it, again, sort of manages to pull itself up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"So this work was a real technical challenge for us,"},{"time":322000,"text":"and we worked very hard, like most of our works, over years"},{"time":325000,"text":"to get the mechanics right and the equilibrium and the dynamics."},{"time":328000,"text":"And it was very important for us"},{"time":330000,"text":"to establish the exact moment that it would fall,"},{"time":333000,"text":"because if we made it in a way that it would topple over,"},{"time":336000,"text":"then it would damage itself,"},{"time":338000,"text":"and if it didn't fall enough, it wouldn't instill that fatalism,"},{"time":341000,"text":"or that sense of wanting to go and help it."},{"time":343000,"text":"So I'm going to show you a very quick video"},{"time":345000,"text":"where we are doing a test scenario -- it's much faster."},{"time":347000,"text":"That's my colleague. He's let it go."},{"time":349000,"text":"Now he's getting nervous, so he's going to go catch it."},{"time":351000,"text":"But he doesn't need to,"},{"time":353000,"text":"because it manages to lift itself up on its own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"So this is a work that we were very intrigued with,"},{"time":358000,"text":"working with the aesthetic of fur"},{"time":360000,"text":"embedded with thousands of tiny different sizes"},{"time":363000,"text":"of fiber optics, which twinkle like the night sky."},{"time":366000,"text":"And it's at the scale of the night sky."},{"time":368000,"text":"So we wrapped this around a blob-like form,"},{"time":370000,"text":"which is in the shape of a teddy bear,"},{"time":372000,"text":"which was hanging from the ceiling."},{"time":374000,"text":"And the idea was to sort of contrast"},{"time":376000,"text":"something very cold and distant and abstract like the universe"},{"time":379000,"text":"into the familiar form of a teddy bear,"},{"time":381000,"text":"which is very comforting and intimate."},{"time":383000,"text":"And the idea was that at some point"},{"time":385000,"text":"you would stop looking at the form of a teddy bear"},{"time":387000,"text":"and you would almost perceive it to be a hole in the space,"},{"time":390000,"text":"and as if you were looking out into the twinkling night sky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"So this is the last work, and a work in progress,"},{"time":396000,"text":"and it's called \"Space Filler.\""},{"time":398000,"text":"Well imagine a small cube that's about this big"},{"time":400000,"text":"standing in front of you in the middle of the room,"},{"time":402000,"text":"and as you approached it, it tried to intimidate you"},{"time":405000,"text":"by growing into a cube"},{"time":407000,"text":"that's twice its height and [eight] times its volume."},{"time":410000,"text":"And so this object is constantly expanding and contracting"},{"time":413000,"text":"to create a dynamic with people moving around it --"},{"time":415000,"text":"almost like it were trying"},{"time":417000,"text":"to conceal a secret within its seams or something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"So we work with a lot of technology,"},{"time":422000,"text":"but we don't really love technology,"},{"time":424000,"text":"because it gives us a lot of pain in our work over years and years."},{"time":427000,"text":"But we use it because we're interested"},{"time":429000,"text":"in the way that it can help us"},{"time":431000,"text":"to express the emotions and behavioral patterns"},{"time":434000,"text":"in these creatures that we create."},{"time":436000,"text":"And once a creature pops into our minds,"},{"time":438000,"text":"it's almost like the process of creation"},{"time":440000,"text":"is to discover the way this creature really wants to exist"},{"time":443000,"text":"and what form it wants to take and what way it wants to move."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}